data.title: Latino and Hispanic Heritage
data.meta_description: The official blog of Audible, Inc.
data.text:
Josh Galarza's debut novel is a touching YA story about overcoming fear, finding friendship, and healing what ails us.

Costa Rican family lore, secrets, and corporate greed provide the kindling for an intriguing work of historical fiction.

In her second novel, Isabel Canas pits a star-crossed young couple against monsters from both Mexican folklore and the real-life history of South Texas.

In her new novel, J.C. Cervantes takes us on a bewitching journey full of Mexican lore and the secret language of flowers.

Hctor Tobar weaves through the US-hispanic diaspora in search of meaning, love for Latin culture, and to finally break free of outdated, restrictive labels.

Whether you're learning the basics or just love hearing the language spoken, this list features Spanish podcasts for listeners of all levels.

Weve collected some of our favorite tales for kids by Latino authors for children to enjoy solo or with the whole family. Listen to culture-rich stories.

Celebrate Hispanic Heritage Month with the works of some of our favorite Afro-Latino authors. Dive into varied cultural experiences and rich storytelling.

Celebra el Mes de la Herencia Latina e Hispana con tus nios escuchando estos espectaculares audiolibros para que conozcan lo mejor de la literatura infantil latinoamericana. Los disfrutars tanto como ellos!
